<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36204g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36204g">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36204g"> 204(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> heathfulizers</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Spiritualism]</font> A man by the name of John Murray Spear <font color="green">[credibly]</font> announced that the eager spirits of the dead had indeed and in truth organised themselves into colleges in order to assist in the regeneration of the earth. There were bands of &ldquo;Governmentizers, Educationizers, Agriculturalizers, <mark>Electrizers,&rdquo; and, apparently, of Fertilizers</mark>, for <font color="green">[ahem!]</font> there were a number of immaculate conceptions during the period. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 29</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
